 and practically useful for teachers and students involved in thinking about and implementing community-based forms of teaching and learning. Classroom Action links teaching and research in genuinely innovative ways, and provides a range of dissemination strategies to inspire broad-based outcomes and impact among a diverse range of knowledge-users. It marks a major advance on the ways in which the relationship among pedagogy, human rights, and community-based learning has hitherto been theorized and practiced. The community-based learning at the centre of Classroom Action prompts a radically new means of thinking about what teachers do in the classroom, and how and why they do it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCommunity and schoolvCase studies. 0aCommunity education. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aArnott, Brendan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBou-Matar, Majdi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCollins, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCunsolo, Ashlee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanyluk, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFenton, Gregory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeble, Ajay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLegassic, Cory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMain, Brendan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcnie, Morvern, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMündel, Ingrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOnuška, Nata